		
		<div id="index-content">
			<h3>About Us:</h3>
			<p>Graduate Indian Student Association (GISA) is a non-profit organization recognized by the <a href="http://gsa.buffalo.edu">Graduate Students Association</a> at the <a href="http://www.buffalo.edu">University at Buffalo</a>.</p>
			<p>University at Buffalo is one of the campuses in the State University of New York system – the SUNY schools. We welcome you to take advantage of UB’s great diversity and large Indian population and participate in the various cultural events, gatherings and parties throughout the year.</p>
			<p>We represent around 900 students. GISA activities include organizing get-togethers and events to bring together the Indian Community and share our proud values. We also give a hand to the incoming students from India by providing temporary accommodation. We strive to make their stay in the new place as comfortable as possible.</p>
			<p>We aim at providing a friendly and pleasant atmosphere to the Indian student community. We promote the awareness of cultural diversity on campus by organizing various cultural and social events.</p>
			<p>Please browse through the information and feel free to offer your comments / suggestions.</p>
			<p></p>
